\pard\f0\fs28 Annual or perennial herbs, rarely shrubs. Leaves usually digitate, petiolate; stipules adnate to the base of the petiole. Flowers in terminal racemes. Calyx bilabiate, divided almost to the base; corolla variously coloured; wings connate at apex; keel beaked; stamens monadelphous. Legume dehiscent, compressed, usually constricted between the seeds. Seeds 3-12, with a sunken hilum.
