\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. L. angustifolius} L., {\i  Sp. Pl.} 721 (1753). Shortly hairy annual 20-80 cm. Leaflets 10-50 × 2-5 mm, linear to linear-spathulate, glabrous above and sparsely villous beneath; stipules linear-subulate. Racemes 10-20 cm; flowers alternate; peduncle 1-3 cm. Upper lip of calyx c. 4 mm, 2-partite, the lower 6-7 mm, irregularly 3-dentate to subentire. Corolla 11-13 mm, blue. Legume shortly hirsute, yellow to black. Seeds 4-6, ellipsoid, smooth and dull, yellow-brown, dark brown or grey with yellow spots.{\i   Light, acid soils. S. Europe}. Bu Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It ?Ju Lu Sa Si Tu [Au Az Cz Ge He Hu Po Rm Rs (C, W)].
